  "markdown_content": "\n## Executive Summary\n\nYannick requested testing of the Vercel MCP connector to understand its capabilities. Manus successfully explored and tested the connector, performed domain availability checks for Y-OS related domains, and retrieved Vercel documentation snippets for Fluid Compute and AI Gateway configurations. A comprehensive capability brief with live data samples was produced.\n\n\n## Context & Intent\n\nTesting new MCP connector integration to evaluate Vercel platform capabilities for potential use in yOS infrastructure\n\n\n## What Was Done\n\nExecuted Vercel MCP connector tools, performed domain availability checks, retrieved specific documentation, compiled capability assessment\n\n\n## Outputs Produced\n\n- [documentation] Vercel Connector Capability Brief — Comprehensive markdown file detailing connector features with live data samples\n\n## Key Decisions & Validations\n\n- Validated Vercel connector functionality for infrastructure automation\n\n## Lessons Learned\n\nWorked well:\n\n- MCP connector integration successful\n- Domain checking and documentation retrieval functional\nDiscoveries:\n\n- Vercel connector supports domain management and configuration documentation access\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- How to integrate deployment triggering\n- Runtime log access implementation\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- Explore deployment automation features\n- Test runtime log retrieval\n- Evaluate integration with yOS infrastructure\n---\nUID: KsfFg1j2AiNX5YEcENpeOu | Model: claude-sonnet-4-20250514 | Cost: $0.0094\n"
